*Example 3: SAP Fiori Elements

**Step 1: Define a Business Object
@EndUser Text.label: 'Sales Order'
define root view entity ZSalesOrder
  as select from vbak
{
  key vbeln,
      kunnr,
      audat,
      netwr,
      @UI.lineItem: [{ position: 10, label: 'Order ID' }]
      vbeln as OrderID,
      @UI.lineItem: [{ position: 20, label: 'Customer' }]
      kunnr as Customer,
      @UI.lineItem: [{ position: 30, label: 'Order Date' }]
      audat as OrderDate,
      @UI.lineItem: [{ position: 40, label: 'Total Amount' }]
      netwr as TotalAmount
}

**Step 2: Create a Fiori Elements Application
-Use the SAP Business Application Studio to create a new Fiori Elements application based on the ZSalesOrder entity.
-Define the UI annotations in the CDS view to enhance the Fiori application.

**Step 3: Implement the Fiori Application Logic
sap.ui.define([
  "sap/ui/core/mvc/Controller"
], function (Controller) {
  "use strict";

  return Controller.extend("my.namespace.controller.SalesOrder", {
    onInit: function () {
      // Initialization logic
    },

    onFilter: function (oEvent) {
      // Filtering logic based on user input
    }
  });
});
